Package jdrasil.graph

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TreeDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The TreeDecomposer Interface describes a class that models an algorithm for computing a tree-decomposition.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bag<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This class models a bag of the tree-decomposition.
    BitSetGraph<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    A BitSetGraph stores a graph (with arbitrary vertices) as bitwise adjacency matrix, i.e., as array of BitSets where the i'th BitSet corresponds to the i'th row of the adjacency matrix.
    Dinic
    A simple Implementation of the Dinic algorithm to compute a max flow.
    Graph<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This class represents a generic directed graph and provides basic methods to modify it.
    GraphFactory
    The GraphFactory provides methods to construct new graph objects: - the empty graph - a graph stored in a .gr file - or from other data (as logical formulas) All methods of this class should be invoked in a static way.
    GraphWriter
    This class provides various methods to print graphs and tree decomposition to different streams.
    TreeDecomposition<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This class models a tree-decomposition of an undirected graph G.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    TreeDecomposition.TreeDecompositionQuality
    This enum defines the quality of a tree-decomposition.
